This last Saturday night a group of 4 of us ended up at bearnos to have a late dinner after walking around for about an hour looking for a good pub to eat that was still serving food as it was almost midnight. The food was actually pretty good, which also could of had to do with all of us being very hungry because we were eating so late. First we ordered drinks and my friend was served hers with what looked like a small fly in it. We immediately showed the waitress and she apologized and quickly made a new one. We just chalked it up to it being summer, people are walking in and out allowing bugs to fly in and sometimes things happen. We ordered our food and when it came out only 1 of us got the correct order. The waitress again apologized and mentioned that 2 of her customers had just walked out on a large bill and she was distracted... ok understandable. But then when we were done my friend ordered a sandwich to go and once again... wrong order! The waitress did let her keep the sandwich free of charge and had the correct sandwich made, but still... really? And that wasnt even the worst of it. After getting the correct sandwich and paying, we went to get out of the booth only to look down at the floor to see a cockroach scurrying across the floor. I really wish I would have taken a picture but at that point I was so shocked and disgusted I just wanted to get out of there.
